---
block_id: 021
name: hub-system-settings
display_name: "Hub System Settings"
version: 1.0.0
category: core
device_role: hub
vendor: fortinet
platform: fortigate
min_fortios: "7.4.0"

description: |
  System settings for SD-WAN hub. Configures location-id for VPN overlay
  identification and ike-tcp-port for IKE over TCP support.

depends_on:
  - block_id: 020
    reason: "System global must be configured first"

provides:
  - hub-system-settings
  - ike-tcp-port-11443

parameters:
  - name: LOCATION_ID
    description: "Hub location ID (typically loopback or 0.0.0.0)"
    type: ip_address
    required: false
    default: "0.0.0.0"
    note: "0.0.0.0 means hub advertises its WAN IP as location"

  - name: IKE_TCP_PORT
    description: "IKE over TCP port (must match spokes)"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 11443

verification:
  commands:
    - "get system settings"
  expected_patterns:
    - "ike-tcp-port: {{IKE_TCP_PORT}}"
    - "location-id: {{LOCATION_ID}}"

rollback:
  commands:
    - "config system settings"
    - "unset location-id"
    - "unset ike-tcp-port"
    - "end"

notes: |
  - location-id accepts IP address format in FortiOS 7.x (verified on hub)
  - location-id 0.0.0.0 allows hub to advertise WAN IP
  - ike-tcp-port 11443 must match spoke configuration
  - Both settings are required for ADVPN overlay
  - GPOT clarification: FortiOS 7.x location-id IS ip_address type, not integer

---

config system settings
    set location-id {{LOCATION_ID}}
    set ike-tcp-port {{IKE_TCP_PORT}}
end
